text: Pinal County is a county in the central part of the U.S. state of Arizona. As of the 2020 census, the population was 425,264, making it Arizona's third-most populous county. The county seat is Florence. The county was founded in 1875. == References == Category:1875 establishments in the United States Category:1870s establishments in Arizona Territory Category:Arizona counties
